    "    ✻",
    "    |",
    "   ▟█▙     Claude Code v2.1.50",
    " ▐▛███▜▌   Sonnet 4.6 · Claude API",
    "▝▜█████▛▘  /data-root/ews/delta-flow",
    "  ▘▘ ▝▝",
    "❯ Add a new IDEA to @IDEAS.md:                                                                                                                   ",
    "  A tool that checks for updats to typical frameworks (e.g. Typo3, Wordpress). That could be archived by also developing an extension that       ",
    "  exposes the current version via /version e.g. Then the tool checks which is the latest version of Typo3 and compaires that with the acutal     ",
    "  server version.                                                                                                                                ",
    "● Read 1 file (ctrl+o to expand)",
    "● Update(api/IDEAS.md)",
    "  ⎿  Added 41 lines",
    "      569  - Blacklist check: query public DNSBL services (Spamhaus, SURBL) via DNS lookups",
    "      570  - No Puppeteer needed — all network-level checks",
    "      571  - Optional token cost: AI-generated \"domain health summary\" narrative",
    "      572 +                                                                                                                                   ",
    "      573 +---                                                                                                                                ",
    "      574 +                                                                                                                                   ",
    "      575 +## Tool 11 — CMS & Framework Version Checker                                                                                       ",
    "      576 +                                                                                                                                   ",
    "      577 +### Description                                                                                                                    ",
    "      578 +Check whether websites running popular CMS platforms or frameworks (e.g., TYPO3, WordPress, Drupal, Joomla) are up to date with    ",
    "          +the latest available version. Outdated software is one of the most common attack vectors — this tool provides instant visibility   ",
    "          +into version currency across any number of sites.                                                                                  ",
    "      579 +                                                                                                                                   ",
    "      580 +### What It Does                                                                                                                   ",
    "      581 +- Accepts one or more target URLs and detects the installed CMS/framework (reusing Technology Detector logic)                      ",
    "      582 +- Retrieves the currently installed version from the target server:                                                                ",
    "      583 +  - **Primary method**: Reads a standardized `/version` endpoint exposed by a companion extension/plugin (see below)               ",
    "      584 +  - **Fallback methods**: Parses version hints from HTML meta tags, generator tags, readme files, changelog paths, or HTTP headers ",
    "          + (e.g., `X-Powered-By: TYPO3 12.4`)                                                                                                ",
    "      585 +- Fetches the latest stable release for each detected platform from its official release feed or API:                              ",
    "      586 +  - WordPress: `api.wordpress.org/core/version-check`                                                                              ",
    "      587 +  - TYPO3: official release RSS/JSON feed or GitHub releases                                                                       ",
    "      588 +  - Drupal, Joomla, etc.: their respective update APIs                                                                             ",
    "      589 +- Compares installed vs. latest version and classifies the gap:                                                                    ",
    "      590 +  - Up to date                                                                                                                     ",
    "      591 +  - Minor update available (patch/security release)                                                                                ",
    "      592 +  - Major update available                                                                                                         ",
    "      593 +  - End-of-life version (no longer receiving security patches)                                                                     ",
    "      594 +- Displays a per-site summary table with version, latest, gap, and EOL status                                                      ",
    "      595 +- Alerts when a site is running an EOL or critically outdated version                                                              ",
    "      596 +                                                                                                                                   ",
    "      597 +### Companion Extension / Plugin (Optional)                                                                                        ",
    "      598 +To ensure reliable, accurate version detection without scraping, a lightweight companion component can be installed on the target  ",
    "          +site:                                                                                                                              ",
    "      599 +- **TYPO3 Extension**: Exposes `GET /version` returning `{ \"cms\": \"typo3\", \"version\": \"12.4.3\" }` — installable via Composer or    ",
    "          +the TYPO3 Extension Repository (TER)                                                                                               ",
    "      600 +- **WordPress Plugin**: Same concept, exposes a REST endpoint `GET /wp-json/delta-flow/v1/version`                                 ",
    "      601 +- The endpoint can optionally be secured with a configurable secret token passed via HTTP header                                   ",
    "      602 +- Without the companion extension, the tool falls back to passive fingerprinting                                                   ",
    "      603 +                                                                                                                                   ",
    "      604 +### Why It's Valuable                                                                                                              ",
    "      605 +Outdated CMS versions are the root cause of a large proportion of website compromises. Agencies managing dozens of client sites    ",
    "          +have no easy way to see at a glance which sites need updates. This tool provides that overview in seconds. The companion extension ",
    "          + model also opens a future path toward deeper site health reporting without requiring admin credentials.                           ",
    "      606 +                                                                                                                                   ",
    "      607 +### Technical Notes                                                                                                                ",
    "      608 +- Version fetching: `node-fetch` or `axios` — no browser automation needed for the `/version` endpoint                             ",
    "      609 +- Passive fingerprinting fallback reuses the `PageHandler.ts` + Wappalyzer-style detection from Tool 6                             ",
    "      610 +- Official release data fetched from public APIs/feeds and cached (e.g., 1-hour TTL) to avoid hammering upstream services          ",
    "      611 +- EOL date data maintained as a static lookup table per platform (updated periodically)                                            ",
    "      612 +- No token cost for the core comparison; optional AI summary of risk level and recommended update path                             ",
    "● Added Tool 11 — CMS & Framework Version Checker to the end of the TOOLS section. It covers:",
    "  - Version detection via a standardized /version endpoint (primary) with passive fingerprinting fallback (HTML meta tags, readme files, HTTP",
